<worksheet xml:id="activity-tutorial-10">
  <title>Tutorial-10</title>
  <introduction>
                <p>
                    Following exercises are taken from Section 14.3 of the book <em>Abstract Algebra</em> by Dummit and Foote.
                </p>
  </introduction>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
        <p>
            Find the factorization of <m>x^8-x</m> over <m>\Z[x]</m> and <m>\F_2[x]</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
        <p>
            Show that an algebraically closed field must be infinite.
        </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
        <p>
            Construct the finite field with <m>16</m> elements as a quotient of <m>\F_2[x]</m> and find a generator for its multiplicative group.
        </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
        <p>
            Find an explicit isomorphism between the splitting fields of <m>x^3-x+1</m> and <m>x^3-x-1</m> over <m>\F_3</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
        <p>
            Let <m>K=\Q\left(\sqrt{D_1},\sqrt{D_2}\right)</m> be a biquadratic extension over <m>\Q</m>, and let <m>\theta\in K</m> be such that <m>K=\Q(\theta)</m>. Show that the minimal polynomial of <m>\theta</m> over <m>\Q</m> is irreducible of degree <m>4</m> but is reducible modulo <m>p</m> for every prime <m>p</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
        <p>
            Show that the splitting field of the polynomial <m>x^p-x-a</m> over <m>\F_p</m>, for <m>0\neq a\in\F_p</m> is cyclic.
        </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
        <p>
            Let <m>p</m> be a prime number and let <m>q=p^n</m>. Denote by <m>\sigma_q</m> the <m>m</m>-th power of the Frobenius automorphism.
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Show that <m>\sigma_q</m> fixes <m>\F_q</m>.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Show that every finite extension of <m>\F_q</m> is Galois with cyclic Galois group generated by <m>\sigma_q</m>.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Prove that <m>n</m> divides <m>\varphi(q-1)</m>.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
        <p>
            Prove that <m>x^{p^n}-x+1</m> is irreducible over <m>\F_p</m> only when <m>n=1</m> or <m>n=p=2</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>
</worksheet>
